Buss acquired, nurtured and befriended a staggering array of talented players and basketball minds during his Hall of Fame tenure.

Few owners in sports history can even approach Buss' accomplishments with the Lakers, who made the NBA finals 16 times through 2011 during his 32 years in charge, winning 10 titles between 1980 and 2010.

The Lakers easily are the NBA's most successful franchise since he bought the club in 1979.

He was also beloved by his players, and often referred to the team as his extended family.

Working with front-office executives 
