Buss earned a Ph.D. in chemistry at age 24 and had careers in aerospace and real estate development before getting into sports.

With money largely from his Santa Monica real-estate ventures, Buss bought the then-struggling Lakers, the NHL's Los Angeles Kings and both clubs' arena - the Forum - from Jack Kent Cooke in a $67.5million deal that was the largest sports transaction in history at the time.=

